3050 /*
3051  * call-seq:
3052  * str =~ obj -> fixnum or nil
3053  *
3054  * Match---If <i>obj</i> is a <code>Regexp</code>, use it as a pattern to match
3055  * against <i>str</i>,and returns the position the match starts, or
3056  * <code>nil</code> if there is no match. Otherwise, invokes
3057  * <i>obj.=~</i>, passing <i>str</i> as an argument. The default
3058  * <code>=~</code> in <code>Object</code> returns <code>nil</code>.
3059  *
3060  * Note: <code>str =~ regexp</code> is not the same as
3061  * <code>regexp =~ str</code>. Strings captured from named capture groups
3062  * are assigned to local variables only in the second case.
3063  *
3064  * "cat o' 9 tails" =~ /\d/ #=> 7
3065  * "cat o' 9 tails" =~ 9 #=> nil
3066  */
3067 
3068 static VALUE
3069 rb_str_match(VALUE x, VALUE y)
3070 {
3071  if (SPECIAL_CONST_P(y)) goto generic;
3072  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(y)) {
3073  case T_STRING:
3074  rb_raise(rb_eTypeError, "type mismatch: String given");
3075 
3076  case T_REGEXP:
3077  return rb_reg_match(y, x);
3078 
3079  generic:
3080  default:
3081  return rb_funcall(y, rb_intern("=~"), 1, x);
3082  }
3083 }
3084 
3085 
3086 static VALUE get_pat(VALUE);
3087 
3088 
3089 /*
3090  * call-seq:
3091  * str.match(pattern) -> matchdata or nil
3092  * str.match(pattern, pos) -> matchdata or nil
3093  *
3094  * Converts <i>pattern</i> to a <code>Regexp</code> (if it isn't already one),
3095  * then invokes its <code>match</code> method on <i>str</i>. If the second
3096  * parameter is present, it specifies the position in the string to begin the
3097  * search.
3098  *
3099  * 'hello'.match('(.)\1') #=> #<MatchData "ll" 1:"l">
3100  * 'hello'.match('(.)\1')[0] #=> "ll"
3101  * 'hello'.match(/(.)\1/)[0] #=> "ll"
3102  * 'hello'.match('xx') #=> nil
3103  *
3104  * If a block is given, invoke the block with MatchData if match succeed, so
3105  * that you can write
3106  *
3107  * str.match(pat) {|m| ...}
3108  *
3109  * instead of
3110  *
3111  * if m = str.match(pat)
3112  * ...
3113  * end
3114  *
3115  * The return value is a value from block execution in this case.
3116  */
3117 
3118 static VALUE
3119 rb_str_match_m(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str)
3120 {
3121  VALUE re, result;
3122  if (argc < 1)
3123  rb_check_arity(argc, 1, 2);
3124  re = argv[0];
3125  argv[0] = str;
3126  result = rb_funcall2(get_pat(re), rb_intern("match"), argc, argv);
3127  if (!NIL_P(result) && rb_block_given_p()) {
3128  return rb_yield(result);
3129  }
3130  return result;
3131 }
3132 
3133 enum neighbor_char {
3134  NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR,
3135  NEIGHBOR_FOUND,
3136  NEIGHBOR_WRAPPED
3137 };
3138 
3139 static enum neighbor_char
3140 enc_succ_char(char *p, long len, rb_encoding *enc)
3141 {
3142  long i;
3143  int l;
3144 
3145  if (rb_enc_mbminlen(enc) > 1) {
3146  /* wchar, trivial case */
3147  int r = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(p, p + len, enc), c;
3148  if (!MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(r)) {
3149  return NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR;
3150  }
3151  c = rb_enc_mbc_to_codepoint(p, p + len, enc) + 1;
3152  l = rb_enc_code_to_mbclen(c, enc);
3153  if (!l) return NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR;
3154  if (l != len) return NEIGHBOR_WRAPPED;
3155  rb_enc_mbcput(c, p, enc);
3156  r = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(p, p + len, enc);
3157  if (!MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(r)) {
3158  return NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR;
3159  }
3160  return NEIGHBOR_FOUND;
3161  }
3162  while (1) {
3163  for (i = len-1; 0 <= i && (unsigned char)p[i] == 0xff; i--)
3164  p[i] = '\0';
3165  if (i < 0)
3166  return NEIGHBOR_WRAPPED;
3167  ++((unsigned char*)p)[i];
3168  l = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(p, p+len, enc);
3169  if (MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(l)) {
3170  l = MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_LEN(l);
3171  if (l == len) {
3172  return NEIGHBOR_FOUND;
3173  }
3174  else {
3175  memset(p+l, 0xff, len-l);
3176  }
3177  }
3178  if (MBCLEN_INVALID_P(l) && i < len-1) {
3179  long len2;
3180  int l2;
3181  for (len2 = len-1; 0 < len2; len2--) {
3182  l2 = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(p, p+len2, enc);
3183  if (!MBCLEN_INVALID_P(l2))
3184  break;
3185  }
3186  memset(p+len2+1, 0xff, len-(len2+1));
3187  }
3188  }
3189 }
3190 
3191 static enum neighbor_char
3192 enc_pred_char(char *p, long len, rb_encoding *enc)
3193 {
3194  long i;
3195  int l;
3196  if (rb_enc_mbminlen(enc) > 1) {
3197  /* wchar, trivial case */
3198  int r = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(p, p + len, enc), c;
3199  if (!MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(r)) {
3200  return NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR;
3201  }
3202  c = rb_enc_mbc_to_codepoint(p, p + len, enc);
3203  if (!c) return NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR;
3204  --c;
3205  l = rb_enc_code_to_mbclen(c, enc);
3206  if (!l) return NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR;
3207  if (l != len) return NEIGHBOR_WRAPPED;
3208  rb_enc_mbcput(c, p, enc);
3209  r = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(p, p + len, enc);
3210  if (!MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(r)) {
3211  return NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR;
3212  }
3213  return NEIGHBOR_FOUND;
3214  }
3215  while (1) {
3216  for (i = len-1; 0 <= i && (unsigned char)p[i] == 0; i--)
3217  p[i] = '\xff';
3218  if (i < 0)
3219  return NEIGHBOR_WRAPPED;
3220  --((unsigned char*)p)[i];
3221  l = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(p, p+len, enc);
3222  if (MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(l)) {
3223  l = MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_LEN(l);
3224  if (l == len) {
3225  return NEIGHBOR_FOUND;
3226  }
3227  else {
3228  memset(p+l, 0, len-l);
3229  }
3230  }
3231  if (MBCLEN_INVALID_P(l) && i < len-1) {
3232  long len2;
3233  int l2;
3234  for (len2 = len-1; 0 < len2; len2--) {
3235  l2 = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(p, p+len2, enc);
3236  if (!MBCLEN_INVALID_P(l2))
3237  break;
3238  }
3239  memset(p+len2+1, 0, len-(len2+1));
3240  }
3241  }
3242 }
3243 
3244 /*
3245  overwrite +p+ by succeeding letter in +enc+ and returns
3246  NEIGHBOR_FOUND or NEIGHBOR_WRAPPED.
3247  When NEIGHBOR_WRAPPED, carried-out letter is stored into carry.
3248  assuming each ranges are successive, and mbclen
3249  never change in each ranges.
3250  NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR is returned if invalid character or the range has only one
3251  character.
3252  */
3253 static enum neighbor_char
3254 enc_succ_alnum_char(char *p, long len, rb_encoding *enc, char *carry)
3255 {
3256  enum neighbor_char ret;
3257  unsigned int c;
3258  int ctype;
3259  int range;
3260  char save[ONIGENC_CODE_TO_MBC_MAXLEN];
3261 
3262  c = rb_enc_mbc_to_codepoint(p, p+len, enc);
3263  if (rb_enc_isctype(c, ONIGENC_CTYPE_DIGIT, enc))
3264  ctype = ONIGENC_CTYPE_DIGIT;
3265  else if (rb_enc_isctype(c, ONIGENC_CTYPE_ALPHA, enc))
3266  ctype = ONIGENC_CTYPE_ALPHA;
3267  else
3268  return NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR;
3269 
3270  MEMCPY(save, p, char, len);
3271  ret = enc_succ_char(p, len, enc);
3272  if (ret == NEIGHBOR_FOUND) {
3273  c = rb_enc_mbc_to_codepoint(p, p+len, enc);
3274  if (rb_enc_isctype(c, ctype, enc))
3275  return NEIGHBOR_FOUND;
3276  }
3277  MEMCPY(p, save, char, len);
3278  range = 1;
3279  while (1) {
3280  MEMCPY(save, p, char, len);
3281  ret = enc_pred_char(p, len, enc);
3282  if (ret == NEIGHBOR_FOUND) {
3283  c = rb_enc_mbc_to_codepoint(p, p+len, enc);
3284  if (!rb_enc_isctype(c, ctype, enc)) {
3285  MEMCPY(p, save, char, len);
3286  break;
3287  }
3288  }
3289  else {
3290  MEMCPY(p, save, char, len);
3291  break;
3292  }
3293  range++;
3294  }
3295  if (range == 1) {
3296  return NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR;
3297  }
3298 
3299  if (ctype != ONIGENC_CTYPE_DIGIT) {
3300  MEMCPY(carry, p, char, len);
3301  return NEIGHBOR_WRAPPED;
3302  }
3303 
3304  MEMCPY(carry, p, char, len);
3305  enc_succ_char(carry, len, enc);
3306  return NEIGHBOR_WRAPPED;
3307 }
3308 
3309 
3310 static VALUE str_succ(VALUE str);
3311 
3312 /*
3313  * call-seq:
3314  * str.succ -> new_str
3315  * str.next -> new_str
3316  *
3317  * Returns the successor to <i>str</i>. The successor is calculated by
3318  * incrementing characters starting from the rightmost alphanumeric (or
3319  * the rightmost character if there are no alphanumerics) in the
3320  * string. Incrementing a digit always results in another digit, and
3321  * incrementing a letter results in another letter of the same case.
3322  * Incrementing nonalphanumerics uses the underlying character set's
3323  * collating sequence.
3324  *
3325  * If the increment generates a ``carry,'' the character to the left of
3326  * it is incremented. This process repeats until there is no carry,
3327  * adding an additional character if necessary.
3328  *
3329  * "abcd".succ #=> "abce"
3330  * "THX1138".succ #=> "THX1139"
3331  * "<<koala>>".succ #=> "<<koalb>>"
3332  * "1999zzz".succ #=> "2000aaa"
3333  * "ZZZ9999".succ #=> "AAAA0000"
3334  * "***".succ #=> "**+"
3335  */
3336 
3337 VALUE
3338 rb_str_succ(VALUE orig)
3339 {
3340  VALUE str;
3341  str = rb_str_new_with_class(orig, RSTRING_PTR(orig), RSTRING_LEN(orig));
3342  rb_enc_cr_str_copy_for_substr(str, orig);
3343  OBJ_INFECT(str, orig);
3344  return str_succ(str);
3345 }
3346 
3347 static VALUE
3348 str_succ(VALUE str)
3349 {
3350  rb_encoding *enc;
3351  char *sbeg, *s, *e, *last_alnum = 0;
3352  int c = -1;
3353  long l, slen;
3354  char carry[ONIGENC_CODE_TO_MBC_MAXLEN] = "\1";
3355  long carry_pos = 0, carry_len = 1;
3356  enum neighbor_char neighbor = NEIGHBOR_FOUND;
3357 
3358  slen = RSTRING_LEN(str);
3359  if (slen == 0) return str;
3360 
3361  enc = STR_ENC_GET(str);
3362  sbeg = RSTRING_PTR(str);
3363  s = e = sbeg + slen;
3364 
3365  while ((s = rb_enc_prev_char(sbeg, s, e, enc)) != 0) {
3366  if (neighbor == NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR && last_alnum) {
3367  if (ISALPHA(*last_alnum) ? ISDIGIT(*s) :
3368  ISDIGIT(*last_alnum) ? ISALPHA(*s) : 0) {
3369  s = last_alnum;
3370  break;
3371  }
3372  }
3373  l = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(s, e, enc);
3374  if (!ONIGENC_MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(l)) continue;
3375  l = ONIGENC_MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_LEN(l);
3376  neighbor = enc_succ_alnum_char(s, l, enc, carry);
3377  switch (neighbor) {
3378  case NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR:
3379  continue;
3380  case NEIGHBOR_FOUND:
3381  return str;
3382  case NEIGHBOR_WRAPPED:
3383  last_alnum = s;
3384  break;
3385  }
3386  c = 1;
3387  carry_pos = s - sbeg;
3388  carry_len = l;
3389  }
3390  if (c == -1) { /* str contains no alnum */
3391  s = e;
3392  while ((s = rb_enc_prev_char(sbeg, s, e, enc)) != 0) {
3393  enum neighbor_char neighbor;
3394  char tmp[ONIGENC_CODE_TO_MBC_MAXLEN];
3395  l = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(s, e, enc);
3396  if (!ONIGENC_MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(l)) continue;
3397  l = ONIGENC_MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_LEN(l);
3398  MEMCPY(tmp, s, char, l);
3399  neighbor = enc_succ_char(tmp, l, enc);
3400  switch (neighbor) {
3401  case NEIGHBOR_FOUND:
3402  MEMCPY(s, tmp, char, l);
3403  return str;
3404  break;
3405  case NEIGHBOR_WRAPPED:
3406  MEMCPY(s, tmp, char, l);
3407  break;
3408  case NEIGHBOR_NOT_CHAR:
3409  break;
3410  }
3411  if (rb_enc_precise_mbclen(s, s+l, enc) != l) {
3412  /* wrapped to \0...\0. search next valid char. */
3413  enc_succ_char(s, l, enc);
3414  }
3415  if (!rb_enc_asciicompat(enc)) {
3416  MEMCPY(carry, s, char, l);
3417  carry_len = l;
3418  }
3419  carry_pos = s - sbeg;
3420  }
3421  }
3422  RESIZE_CAPA(str, slen + carry_len);
3423  sbeg = RSTRING_PTR(str);
3424  s = sbeg + carry_pos;
3425  memmove(s + carry_len, s, slen - carry_pos);
3426  memmove(s, carry, carry_len);
3427  slen += carry_len;
3428  STR_SET_LEN(str, slen);
3429  TERM_FILL(&sbeg[slen], rb_enc_mbminlen(enc));
3430  rb_enc_str_coderange(str);
3431  return str;
3432 }
3433 
3434 
3435 /*
3436  * call-seq:
3437  * str.succ! -> str
3438  * str.next! -> str
3439  *
3440  * Equivalent to <code>String#succ</code>, but modifies the receiver in
3441  * place.
3442  */
3443 
3444 static VALUE
3445 rb_str_succ_bang(VALUE str)
3446 {
3447  rb_str_modify(str);
3448  str_succ(str);
3449  return str;
3450 }
3451 
3452 static int
3453 all_digits_p(const char *s, long len)
3454 {
3455  while (len-- > 0) {
3456  if (!ISDIGIT(*s)) return 0;
3457  s++;
3458  }
3459  return 1;
3460 }
3461 
3462 static VALUE str_upto_each(VALUE beg, VALUE end, int excl, int (*each)(VALUE, VALUE), VALUE);
3463 
3464 static int
3465 str_upto_i(VALUE str, VALUE arg)
3466 {
3467  rb_yield(str);
3468  return 0;
3469 }
3470 
3471 /*
3472  * call-seq:
3473  * str.upto(other_str, exclusive=false) {|s| block } -> str
3474  * str.upto(other_str, exclusive=false) -> an_enumerator
3475  *
3476  * Iterates through successive values, starting at <i>str</i> and
3477  * ending at <i>other_str</i> inclusive, passing each value in turn to
3478  * the block. The <code>String#succ</code> method is used to generate
3479  * each value. If optional second argument exclusive is omitted or is false,
3480  * the last value will be included; otherwise it will be excluded.
3481  *
3482  * If no block is given, an enumerator is returned instead.
3483  *
3484  * "a8".upto("b6") {|s| print s, ' ' }
3485  * for s in "a8".."b6"
3486  * print s, ' '
3487  * end
3488  *
3489  * <em>produces:</em>
3490  *
3491  * a8 a9 b0 b1 b2 b3 b4 b5 b6
3492  * a8 a9 b0 b1 b2 b3 b4 b5 b6
3493  *
3494  * If <i>str</i> and <i>other_str</i> contains only ascii numeric characters,
3495  * both are recognized as decimal numbers. In addition, the width of
3496  * string (e.g. leading zeros) is handled appropriately.
3497  *
3498  * "9".upto("11").to_a #=> ["9", "10", "11"]
3499  * "25".upto("5").to_a #=> []
3500  * "07".upto("11").to_a #=> ["07", "08", "09", "10", "11"]
3501  */
3502 
3503 static VALUE
3504 rb_str_upto(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE beg)
3505 {
3506  VALUE end, exclusive;
3507 
3508  rb_scan_args(argc, argv, "11", &end, &exclusive);
3509  RETURN_ENUMERATOR(beg, argc, argv);
3510  return str_upto_each(beg, end, RTEST(exclusive), str_upto_i, Qnil);
3511 }
3512 
3513 static VALUE
3514 str_upto_each(VALUE beg, VALUE end, int excl, int (*each)(VALUE, VALUE), VALUE arg)
3515 {
3516  VALUE current, after_end;
3517  ID succ;
3518  int n, ascii;
3519  rb_encoding *enc;
3520 
3521  CONST_ID(succ, "succ");
3522  StringValue(end);
3523  enc = rb_enc_check(beg, end);
3524  ascii = (is_ascii_string(beg) && is_ascii_string(end));
3525  /* single character */
3526  if (RSTRING_LEN(beg) == 1 && RSTRING_LEN(end) == 1 && ascii) {
3527  char c = RSTRING_PTR(beg)[0];
3528  char e = RSTRING_PTR(end)[0];
3529 
3530  if (c > e || (excl && c == e)) return beg;
3531  for (;;) {
3532  if ((*each)(rb_enc_str_new(&c, 1, enc), arg)) break;
3533  if (!excl && c == e) break;
3534  c++;
3535  if (excl && c == e) break;
3536  }
3537  return beg;
3538  }
3539  /* both edges are all digits */
3540  if (ascii && ISDIGIT(RSTRING_PTR(beg)[0]) && ISDIGIT(RSTRING_PTR(end)[0]) &&
3541  all_digits_p(RSTRING_PTR(beg), RSTRING_LEN(beg)) &&
3542  all_digits_p(RSTRING_PTR(end), RSTRING_LEN(end))) {
3543  VALUE b, e;
3544  int width;
3545 
3546  width = RSTRING_LENINT(beg);
3547  b = rb_str_to_inum(beg, 10, FALSE);
3548  e = rb_str_to_inum(end, 10, FALSE);
3549  if (FIXNUM_P(b) && FIXNUM_P(e)) {
3550  long bi = FIX2LONG(b);
3551  long ei = FIX2LONG(e);
3552  rb_encoding *usascii = rb_usascii_encoding();
3553 
3554  while (bi <= ei) {
3555  if (excl && bi == ei) break;
3556  if ((*each)(rb_enc_sprintf(usascii, "%.*ld", width, bi), arg)) break;
3557  bi++;
3558  }
3559  }
3560  else {
3561  ID op = excl ? '<' : rb_intern("<=");
3562  VALUE args[2], fmt = rb_obj_freeze(rb_usascii_str_new_cstr("%.*d"));
3563 
3564  args[0] = INT2FIX(width);
3565  while (rb_funcall(b, op, 1, e)) {
3566  args[1] = b;
3567  if ((*each)(rb_str_format(numberof(args), args, fmt), arg)) break;
3568  b = rb_funcallv(b, succ, 0, 0);
3569  }
3570  }
3571  return beg;
3572  }
3573  /* normal case */
3574  n = rb_str_cmp(beg, end);
3575  if (n > 0 || (excl && n == 0)) return beg;
3576 
3577  after_end = rb_funcallv(end, succ, 0, 0);
3578  current = rb_str_dup(beg);
3579  while (!rb_str_equal(current, after_end)) {
3580  VALUE next = Qnil;
3581  if (excl || !rb_str_equal(current, end))
3582  next = rb_funcallv(current, succ, 0, 0);
3583  if ((*each)(current, arg)) break;
3584  if (NIL_P(next)) break;
3585  current = next;
3586  StringValue(current);
3587  if (excl && rb_str_equal(current, end)) break;
3588  if (RSTRING_LEN(current) > RSTRING_LEN(end) || RSTRING_LEN(current) == 0)
3589  break;
3590  }
3591 
3592  return beg;
3593 }
3594 
3595 static int
3596 include_range_i(VALUE str, VALUE arg)
3597 {
3598  VALUE *argp = (VALUE *)arg;
3599  if (!rb_equal(str, *argp)) return 0;
3600  *argp = Qnil;
3601  return 1;
3602 }

3604 VALUE

3606 {

3608  StringValue(end);
3609  end = rb_str_new_frozen(end);
3610  if (NIL_P(val)) return Qfalse;
3611  val = rb_check_string_type(val);
3612  if (NIL_P(val)) return Qfalse;
3613  if (rb_enc_asciicompat(STR_ENC_GET(beg)) &&
3614  rb_enc_asciicompat(STR_ENC_GET(end)) &&
3615  rb_enc_asciicompat(STR_ENC_GET(val))) {
3616  const char *bp = RSTRING_PTR(beg);

3618  const char *vp = RSTRING_PTR(val);

3620  if (RSTRING_LEN(val) == 0 || RSTRING_LEN(val) > 1)

3622  else {
3623  char b = *bp;
3624  char e = *ep;

3628  if (b <= v && v < e) return Qtrue;

3632  }
3633  }
3634 #if 0

3636  if (ISDIGIT(*bp) && ISDIGIT(*ep) &&
3637  all_digits_p(bp, RSTRING_LEN(beg)) &&
3638  all_digits_p(ep, RSTRING_LEN(end))) {
3639  /* TODO */
3640  }
3641 #endif
3642  }
3643  str_upto_each(beg, end, RTEST(exclusive), include_range_i, (VALUE)&val);
3644 
3645  return NIL_P(val) ? Qtrue : Qfalse;
3646 }

3648 static VALUE
3649 rb_str_subpat(VALUE str, VALUE re, VALUE backref)
3650 {
3651  if (rb_reg_search(re, str, 0, 0) >= 0) {
3652  VALUE match = rb_backref_get();
3653  int nth = rb_reg_backref_number(match, backref);
3654  return rb_reg_nth_match(nth, match);
3655  }
3656  return Qnil;
3657 }
3658 
3659 static VALUE
3660 rb_str_aref(VALUE str, VALUE indx)
3661 {
3662  long idx;
3663 
3664  if (FIXNUM_P(indx)) {
3665  idx = FIX2LONG(indx);
3666 
3667  num_index:
3668  str = rb_str_substr(str, idx, 1);
3669  if (!NIL_P(str) && RSTRING_LEN(str) == 0) return Qnil;
3670  return str;
3671  }
3672 
3673  if (SPECIAL_CONST_P(indx)) goto generic;
3674  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(indx)) {
3675  case T_REGEXP:
3676  return rb_str_subpat(str, indx, INT2FIX(0));
3677 
3678  case T_STRING:
3679  if (rb_str_index(str, indx, 0) != -1)
3680  return rb_str_dup(indx);
3681  return Qnil;
3682 
3683  generic:
3684  default:
3685  /* check if indx is Range */
3686  {
3687  long beg, len;
3688  VALUE tmp;
3689 
3690  len = str_strlen(str, NULL);
3691  switch (rb_range_beg_len(indx, &beg, &len, len, 0)) {
3692  case Qfalse:
3693  break;
3694  case Qnil:
3695  return Qnil;
3696  default:
3697  tmp = rb_str_substr(str, beg, len);
3698  return tmp;
3699  }
3700  }
3701  idx = NUM2LONG(indx);
3702  goto num_index;
3703  }
3704 
3705  UNREACHABLE;
3706 }
3707 
3708 
3709 /*
3710  * call-seq:
3711  * str[index] -> new_str or nil
3712  * str[start, length] -> new_str or nil
3713  * str[range] -> new_str or nil
3714  * str[regexp] -> new_str or nil
3715  * str[regexp, capture] -> new_str or nil
3716  * str[match_str] -> new_str or nil
3717  * str.slice(index) -> new_str or nil
3718  * str.slice(start, length) -> new_str or nil
3719  * str.slice(range) -> new_str or nil
3720  * str.slice(regexp) -> new_str or nil
3721  * str.slice(regexp, capture) -> new_str or nil
3722  * str.slice(match_str) -> new_str or nil
3723  *
3724  * Element Reference --- If passed a single +index+, returns a substring of
3725  * one character at that index. If passed a +start+ index and a +length+,
3726  * returns a substring containing +length+ characters starting at the
3727  * +index+. If passed a +range+, its beginning and end are interpreted as
3728  * offsets delimiting the substring to be returned.
3729  *
3730  * In these three cases, if an index is negative, it is counted from the end
3731  * of the string. For the +start+ and +range+ cases the starting index
3732  * is just before a character and an index matching the string's size.
3733  * Additionally, an empty string is returned when the starting index for a
3734  * character range is at the end of the string.
3735  *
3736  * Returns +nil+ if the initial index falls outside the string or the length
3737  * is negative.
3738  *
3739  * If a +Regexp+ is supplied, the matching portion of the string is
3740  * returned. If a +capture+ follows the regular expression, which may be a
3741  * capture group index or name, follows the regular expression that component
3742  * of the MatchData is returned instead.
3743  *
3744  * If a +match_str+ is given, that string is returned if it occurs in
3745  * the string.
3746  *
3747  * Returns +nil+ if the regular expression does not match or the match string
3748  * cannot be found.
3749  *
3750  * a = "hello there"
3751  *
3752  * a[1] #=> "e"
3753  * a[2, 3] #=> "llo"
3754  * a[2..3] #=> "ll"
3755  *
3756  * a[-3, 2] #=> "er"
3757  * a[7..-2] #=> "her"
3758  * a[-4..-2] #=> "her"
3759  * a[-2..-4] #=> ""
3760  *
3761  * a[11, 0] #=> ""
3762  * a[11] #=> nil
3763  * a[12, 0] #=> nil
3764  * a[12..-1] #=> nil
3765  *
3766  * a[/[aeiou](.)\1/] #=> "ell"
3767  * a[/[aeiou](.)\1/, 0] #=> "ell"
3768  * a[/[aeiou](.)\1/, 1] #=> "l"
3769  * a[/[aeiou](.)\1/, 2] #=> nil
3770  *
3771  * a[/(?<vowel>[aeiou])(?<non_vowel>[^aeiou])/, "non_vowel"] #=> "l"
3772  * a[/(?<vowel>[aeiou])(?<non_vowel>[^aeiou])/, "vowel"] #=> "e"
3773  *
3774  * a["lo"] #=> "lo"
3775  * a["bye"] #=> nil
3776  */
3777 
3778 static VALUE
3779 rb_str_aref_m(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str)
3780 {
3781  if (argc == 2) {
3782  if (RB_TYPE_P(argv[0], T_REGEXP)) {
3783  return rb_str_subpat(str, argv[0], argv[1]);
3784  }
3785  return rb_str_substr(str, NUM2LONG(argv[0]), NUM2LONG(argv[1]));
3786  }
3787  rb_check_arity(argc, 1, 2);
3788  return rb_str_aref(str, argv[0]);
3789 }
3790 
3791 VALUE
3792 rb_str_drop_bytes(VALUE str, long len)
3793 {
3794  char *ptr = RSTRING_PTR(str);
3795  long olen = RSTRING_LEN(str), nlen;
3796 
3797  str_modifiable(str);
3798  if (len > olen) len = olen;
3799  nlen = olen - len;
3800  if (nlen <= RSTRING_EMBED_LEN_MAX) {
3801  char *oldptr = ptr;
3802  int fl = (int)(RBASIC(str)->flags & (STR_NOEMBED|STR_SHARED|STR_NOFREE));
3803  STR_SET_EMBED(str);
3804  STR_SET_EMBED_LEN(str, nlen);
3805  ptr = RSTRING(str)->as.ary;
3806  memmove(ptr, oldptr + len, nlen);
3807  if (fl == STR_NOEMBED) xfree(oldptr);
3808  }
3809  else {
3810  if (!STR_SHARED_P(str)) rb_str_new_frozen(str);
3811  ptr = RSTRING(str)->as.heap.ptr += len;
3812  RSTRING(str)->as.heap.len = nlen;
3813  }
3814  ptr[nlen] = 0;
3815  ENC_CODERANGE_CLEAR(str);
3816  return str;
3817 }
3818 
3819 static void
3820 rb_str_splice_0(VALUE str, long beg, long len, VALUE val)
3821 {
3822  char *sptr;
3823  long slen, vlen = RSTRING_LEN(val);
3824 
3825  if (beg == 0 && vlen == 0) {
3826  rb_str_drop_bytes(str, len);
3827  OBJ_INFECT(str, val);
3828  return;
3829  }
3830 
3831  rb_str_modify(str);
3832  RSTRING_GETMEM(str, sptr, slen);
3833  if (len < vlen) {
3834  /* expand string */
3835  RESIZE_CAPA(str, slen + vlen - len);
3836  sptr = RSTRING_PTR(str);
3837  }
3838 
3839  if (vlen != len) {
3840  memmove(sptr + beg + vlen,
3841  sptr + beg + len,
3842  slen - (beg + len));
3843  }
3844  if (vlen < beg && len < 0) {
3845  MEMZERO(sptr + slen, char, -len);
3846  }
3847  if (vlen > 0) {
3848  memmove(sptr + beg, RSTRING_PTR(val), vlen);
3849  }
3850  slen += vlen - len;
3851  STR_SET_LEN(str, slen);
3852  TERM_FILL(&sptr[slen], TERM_LEN(str));
3853  OBJ_INFECT(str, val);
3854 }
3855 
3856 void
3857 rb_str_update(VALUE str, long beg, long len, VALUE val)
3858 {
3859  long slen;
3860  char *p, *e;
3861  rb_encoding *enc;
3862  int singlebyte = single_byte_optimizable(str);
3863  int cr;
3864 
3865  if (len < 0) rb_raise(rb_eIndexError, "negative length %ld", len);
3866 
3867  StringValue(val);
3868  enc = rb_enc_check(str, val);
3869  slen = str_strlen(str, enc); /* rb_enc_check */
3870 
3871  if (slen < beg) {
3872  out_of_range:
3873  rb_raise(rb_eIndexError, "index %ld out of string", beg);
3874  }
3875  if (beg < 0) {
3876  if (-beg > slen) {
3877  goto out_of_range;
3878  }
3879  beg += slen;
3880  }
3881  if (slen < len || slen < beg + len) {
3882  len = slen - beg;
3883  }
3884  str_modify_keep_cr(str);
3885  p = str_nth(RSTRING_PTR(str), RSTRING_END(str), beg, enc, singlebyte);
3886  if (!p) p = RSTRING_END(str);
3887  e = str_nth(p, RSTRING_END(str), len, enc, singlebyte);
3888  if (!e) e = RSTRING_END(str);
3889  /* error check */
3890  beg = p - RSTRING_PTR(str); /* physical position */
3891  len = e - p; /* physical length */
3892  rb_str_splice_0(str, beg, len, val);
3893  rb_enc_associate(str, enc);
3894  cr = ENC_CODERANGE_AND(ENC_CODERANGE(str), ENC_CODERANGE(val));
3895  if (cr != ENC_CODERANGE_BROKEN)
3896  ENC_CODERANGE_SET(str, cr);
3897 }
3898 
3899 #define rb_str_splice(str, beg, len, val) rb_str_update(str, beg, len, val)
3900 
3901 static void
3902 rb_str_subpat_set(VALUE str, VALUE re, VALUE backref, VALUE val)
3903 {
3904  int nth;
3905  VALUE match;
3906  long start, end, len;
3907  rb_encoding *enc;
3908  struct re_registers *regs;
3909 
3910  if (rb_reg_search(re, str, 0, 0) < 0) {
3911  rb_raise(rb_eIndexError, "regexp not matched");
3912  }
3913  match = rb_backref_get();
3914  nth = rb_reg_backref_number(match, backref);
3915  regs = RMATCH_REGS(match);
3916  if (nth >= regs->num_regs) {
3917  out_of_range:
3918  rb_raise(rb_eIndexError, "index %d out of regexp", nth);
3919  }
3920  if (nth < 0) {
3921  if (-nth >= regs->num_regs) {
3922  goto out_of_range;
3923  }
3924  nth += regs->num_regs;
3925  }
3926 
3927  start = BEG(nth);
3928  if (start == -1) {
3929  rb_raise(rb_eIndexError, "regexp group %d not matched", nth);
3930  }
3931  end = END(nth);
3932  len = end - start;
3933  StringValue(val);
3934  enc = rb_enc_check(str, val);
3935  rb_str_splice_0(str, start, len, val);
3936  rb_enc_associate(str, enc);
3937 }
3938 
3939 static VALUE
3940 rb_str_aset(VALUE str, VALUE indx, VALUE val)
3941 {
3942  long idx, beg;
3943 
3944  if (FIXNUM_P(indx)) {
3945  idx = FIX2LONG(indx);
3946  num_index:
3947  rb_str_splice(str, idx, 1, val);
3948  return val;
3949  }
3950 
3951  if (SPECIAL_CONST_P(indx)) goto generic;
3952  switch (TYPE(indx)) {
3953  case T_REGEXP:
3954  rb_str_subpat_set(str, indx, INT2FIX(0), val);
3955  return val;
3956 
3957  case T_STRING:
3958  beg = rb_str_index(str, indx, 0);
3959  if (beg < 0) {
3960  rb_raise(rb_eIndexError, "string not matched");
3961  }
3962  beg = rb_str_sublen(str, beg);
3963  rb_str_splice(str, beg, str_strlen(indx, NULL), val);
3964  return val;
3965 
3966  generic:
3967  default:
3968  /* check if indx is Range */
3969  {
3970  long beg, len;
3971  if (rb_range_beg_len(indx, &beg, &len, str_strlen(str, NULL), 2)) {
3972  rb_str_splice(str, beg, len, val);
3973  return val;
3974  }
3975  }
3976  idx = NUM2LONG(indx);
3977  goto num_index;
3978  }
3979 }
3980 
3981 /*
3982  * call-seq:
3983  * str[fixnum] = new_str
3984  * str[fixnum, fixnum] = new_str
3985  * str[range] = aString
3986  * str[regexp] = new_str
3987  * str[regexp, fixnum] = new_str
3988  * str[regexp, name] = new_str
3989  * str[other_str] = new_str
3990  *
3991  * Element Assignment---Replaces some or all of the content of <i>str</i>. The
3992  * portion of the string affected is determined using the same criteria as
3993  * <code>String#[]</code>. If the replacement string is not the same length as
3994  * the text it is replacing, the string will be adjusted accordingly. If the
3995  * regular expression or string is used as the index doesn't match a position
3996  * in the string, <code>IndexError</code> is raised. If the regular expression
3997  * form is used, the optional second <code>Fixnum</code> allows you to specify
3998  * which portion of the match to replace (effectively using the
3999  * <code>MatchData</code> indexing rules. The forms that take a
4000  * <code>Fixnum</code> will raise an <code>IndexError</code> if the value is
4001  * out of range; the <code>Range</code> form will raise a
4002  * <code>RangeError</code>, and the <code>Regexp</code> and <code>String</code>
4003  * will raise an <code>IndexError</code> on negative match.
4004  */
4005 
4006 static VALUE
4007 rb_str_aset_m(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str)
4008 {
4009  if (argc == 3) {
4010  if (RB_TYPE_P(argv[0], T_REGEXP)) {
4011  rb_str_subpat_set(str, argv[0], argv[1], argv[2]);
4012  }
4013  else {
4014  rb_str_splice(str, NUM2LONG(argv[0]), NUM2LONG(argv[1]), argv[2]);
4015  }
4016  return argv[2];
4017  }
4018  rb_check_arity(argc, 2, 3);
4019  return rb_str_aset(str, argv[0], argv[1]);
4020 }
4021 
4022 /*
4023  * call-seq:
4024  * str.insert(index, other_str) -> str
4025  *
4026  * Inserts <i>other_str</i> before the character at the given
4027  * <i>index</i>, modifying <i>str</i>. Negative indices count from the
4028  * end of the string, and insert <em>after</em> the given character.
4029  * The intent is insert <i>aString</i> so that it starts at the given
4030  * <i>index</i>.
4031  *
4032  * "abcd".insert(0, 'X') #=> "Xabcd"
4033  * "abcd".insert(3, 'X') #=> "abcXd"
4034  * "abcd".insert(4, 'X') #=> "abcdX"
4035  * "abcd".insert(-3, 'X') #=> "abXcd"
4036  * "abcd".insert(-1, 'X') #=> "abcdX"
4037  */
4038 
4039 static VALUE
4040 rb_str_insert(VALUE str, VALUE idx, VALUE str2)
4041 {
4042  long pos = NUM2LONG(idx);
4043 
4044  if (pos == -1) {
4045  return rb_str_append(str, str2);
4046  }
4047  else if (pos < 0) {
4048  pos++;
4049  }
4050  rb_str_splice(str, pos, 0, str2);
4051  return str;
4052 }
4053 
4054 
4055 /*
4056  * call-seq:
4057  * str.slice!(fixnum) -> new_str or nil
4058  * str.slice!(fixnum, fixnum) -> new_str or nil
4059  * str.slice!(range) -> new_str or nil
4060  * str.slice!(regexp) -> new_str or nil
4061  * str.slice!(other_str) -> new_str or nil
4062  *
4063  * Deletes the specified portion from <i>str</i>, and returns the portion
4064  * deleted.
4065  *
4066  * string = "this is a string"
4067  * string.slice!(2) #=> "i"
4068  * string.slice!(3..6) #=> " is "
4069  * string.slice!(/s.*t/) #=> "sa st"
4070  * string.slice!("r") #=> "r"
4071  * string #=> "thing"
4072  */
4073 
4074 static VALUE
4075 rb_str_slice_bang(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str)
4076 {
4077  VALUE result;
4078  VALUE buf[3];
4079  int i;
4080 
4081  rb_check_arity(argc, 1, 2);
4082  for (i=0; i<argc; i++) {
4083  buf[i] = argv[i];
4084  }
4085  str_modify_keep_cr(str);
4086  result = rb_str_aref_m(argc, buf, str);
4087  if (!NIL_P(result)) {
4088  buf[i] = rb_str_new(0,0);
4089  rb_str_aset_m(argc+1, buf, str);
4090  }
4091  return result;
4092 }

4094 static VALUE
4095 get_pat(VALUE pat)
4096 {
4097  VALUE val;
4098 
4099  if (SPECIAL_CONST_P(pat)) goto to_string;
4100  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(pat)) {
4101  case T_REGEXP:
4102  return pat;
4103 
4104  case T_STRING:
4105  break;
4106 
4107  default:
4108  to_string:
4109  val = rb_check_string_type(pat);
4110  if (NIL_P(val)) {
4111  Check_Type(pat, T_REGEXP);
4112  }
4113  pat = val;
4114  }
4115 
4116  return rb_reg_regcomp(pat);
4117 }
4118 
4119 static VALUE
4120 get_pat_quoted(VALUE pat, int check)
4121 {
4122  VALUE val;
4123 
4124  if (SPECIAL_CONST_P(pat)) goto to_string;
4125  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(pat)) {
4126  case T_REGEXP:
4127  return pat;
4128 
4129  case T_STRING:
4130  break;
4131 
4132  default:
4133  to_string:
4134  val = rb_check_string_type(pat);
4135  if (NIL_P(val)) {
4136  Check_Type(pat, T_REGEXP);
4137  }
4138  pat = val;
4139  }
4140  if (check && is_broken_string(pat)) {
4141  rb_exc_raise(rb_reg_check_preprocess(pat));
4142  }
4143  return pat;
4144 }

4146 static long
4147 rb_pat_search(VALUE pat, VALUE str, long pos, int set_backref_str)
4148 {
4149  if (BUILTIN_TYPE(pat) == T_STRING) {
4150  pos = rb_strseq_index(str, pat, pos, 1);
4151  if (set_backref_str) {
4152  if (pos >= 0) {
4153  VALUE match;
4154  str = rb_str_new_frozen(str);
4155  rb_backref_set_string(str, pos, RSTRING_LEN(pat));
4156  match = rb_backref_get();
4157  OBJ_INFECT(match, pat);
4158  }
4159  else {
4160  rb_backref_set(Qnil);
4161  }
4162  }
4163  return pos;
4164  }
4165  else {
4166  return rb_reg_search0(pat, str, pos, 0, set_backref_str);
4167  }
4168 }

4170 
4171 /*
4172  * call-seq:
4173  * str.sub!(pattern, replacement) -> str or nil
4174  * str.sub!(pattern) {|match| block } -> str or nil
4175  *
4176  * Performs the same substitution as String#sub in-place.
4177  *
4178  * Returns +str+ if a substitution was performed or +nil+ if no substitution
4179  * was performed.
4180  */
4181 
4182 static VALUE
4183 rb_str_sub_bang(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str)
4184 {
4185  VALUE pat, repl, hash = Qnil;
4186  int iter = 0;
4187  int tainted = 0;
4188  long plen;
4189  int min_arity = rb_block_given_p() ? 1 : 2;
4190  long beg;
4191 
4192  rb_check_arity(argc, min_arity, 2);
4193  if (argc == 1) {
4194  iter = 1;
4195  }
4196  else {
4197  repl = argv[1];
4198  hash = rb_check_hash_type(argv[1]);
4199  if (NIL_P(hash)) {
4200  StringValue(repl);
4201  }
4202  if (OBJ_TAINTED(repl)) tainted = 1;
4203  }
4204 
4205  pat = get_pat_quoted(argv[0], 1);
4206 
4207  str_modifiable(str);
4208  beg = rb_pat_search(pat, str, 0, 1);
4209  if (beg >= 0) {
4210  rb_encoding *enc;
4211  int cr = ENC_CODERANGE(str);
4212  long beg0, end0;
4213  VALUE match, match0 = Qnil;
4214  struct re_registers *regs;
4215  char *p, *rp;
4216  long len, rlen;
4217 
4218  match = rb_backref_get();
4219  regs = RMATCH_REGS(match);
4220  if (RB_TYPE_P(pat, T_STRING)) {
4221  beg0 = beg;
4222  end0 = beg0 + RSTRING_LEN(pat);
4223  match0 = pat;
4224  }
4225  else {
4226  beg0 = BEG(0);
4227  end0 = END(0);
4228  if (iter) match0 = rb_reg_nth_match(0, match);
4229  }
4230 
4231  if (iter || !NIL_P(hash)) {
4232  p = RSTRING_PTR(str); len = RSTRING_LEN(str);
4233 
4234  if (iter) {
4235  repl = rb_obj_as_string(rb_yield(match0));
4236  }
4237  else {
4238  repl = rb_hash_aref(hash, rb_str_subseq(str, beg0, end0 - beg0));
4239  repl = rb_obj_as_string(repl);
4240  }
4241  str_mod_check(str, p, len);
4242  rb_check_frozen(str);
4243  }
4244  else {
4245  repl = rb_reg_regsub(repl, str, regs, RB_TYPE_P(pat, T_STRING) ? Qnil : pat);
4246  }
4247 
4248  enc = rb_enc_compatible(str, repl);
4249  if (!enc) {
4250  rb_encoding *str_enc = STR_ENC_GET(str);
4251  p = RSTRING_PTR(str); len = RSTRING_LEN(str);
4252  if (coderange_scan(p, beg0, str_enc) != ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT ||
4253  coderange_scan(p+end0, len-end0, str_enc) != ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT) {
4254  rb_raise(rb_eEncCompatError, "incompatible character encodings: %s and %s",
4255  rb_enc_name(str_enc),
4256  rb_enc_name(STR_ENC_GET(repl)));
4257  }
4258  enc = STR_ENC_GET(repl);
4259  }
4260  rb_str_modify(str);
4261  rb_enc_associate(str, enc);
4262  if (OBJ_TAINTED(repl)) tainted = 1;
4263  if (ENC_CODERANGE_UNKNOWN < cr && cr < ENC_CODERANGE_BROKEN) {
4264  int cr2 = ENC_CODERANGE(repl);
4265  if (cr2 == ENC_CODERANGE_BROKEN ||
4266  (cr == ENC_CODERANGE_VALID && cr2 == ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT))
4267  cr = ENC_CODERANGE_UNKNOWN;
4268  else
4269  cr = cr2;
4270  }
4271  plen = end0 - beg0;
4272  rp = RSTRING_PTR(repl); rlen = RSTRING_LEN(repl);
4273  len = RSTRING_LEN(str);
4274  if (rlen > plen) {
4275  RESIZE_CAPA(str, len + rlen - plen);
4276  }
4277  p = RSTRING_PTR(str);
4278  if (rlen != plen) {
4279  memmove(p + beg0 + rlen, p + beg0 + plen, len - beg0 - plen);
4280  }
4281  memcpy(p + beg0, rp, rlen);
4282  len += rlen - plen;
4283  STR_SET_LEN(str, len);
4284  TERM_FILL(&RSTRING_PTR(str)[len], TERM_LEN(str));
4285  ENC_CODERANGE_SET(str, cr);
4286  if (tainted) OBJ_TAINT(str);
4287 
4288  return str;
4289  }
4290  return Qnil;
4291 }
4292 
4293 
4294 /*
4295  * call-seq:
4296  * str.sub(pattern, replacement) -> new_str
4297  * str.sub(pattern, hash) -> new_str
4298  * str.sub(pattern) {|match| block } -> new_str
4299  *
4300  * Returns a copy of +str+ with the _first_ occurrence of +pattern+
4301  * replaced by the second argument. The +pattern+ is typically a Regexp; if
4302  * given as a String, any regular expression metacharacters it contains will
4303  * be interpreted literally, e.g. <code>'\\\d'</code> will match a backlash
4304  * followed by 'd', instead of a digit.
4305  *
4306  * If +replacement+ is a String it will be substituted for the matched text.
4307  * It may contain back-references to the pattern's capture groups of the form
4308  * <code>"\\d"</code>, where <i>d</i> is a group number, or
4309  * <code>"\\k<n>"</code>, where <i>n</i> is a group name. If it is a
4310  * double-quoted string, both back-references must be preceded by an
4311  * additional backslash. However, within +replacement+ the special match
4312  * variables, such as <code>&$</code>, will not refer to the current match.
4313  * If +replacement+ is a String that looks like a pattern's capture group but
4314  * is actaully not a pattern capture group e.g. <code>"\\'"</code>, then it
4315  * will have to be preceded by two backslashes like so <code>"\\\\'"</code>.
4316  *
4317  * If the second argument is a Hash, and the matched text is one of its keys,
4318  * the corresponding value is the replacement string.
4319  *
4320  * In the block form, the current match string is passed in as a parameter,
4321  * and variables such as <code>$1</code>, <code>$2</code>, <code>$`</code>,
4322  * <code>$&</code>, and <code>$'</code> will be set appropriately. The value
4323  * returned by the block will be substituted for the match on each call.
4324  *
4325  * The result inherits any tainting in the original string or any supplied
4326  * replacement string.
4327  *
4328  * "hello".sub(/[aeiou]/, '*') #=> "h*llo"
4329  * "hello".sub(/([aeiou])/, '<\1>') #=> "h<e>llo"
4330  * "hello".sub(/./) {|s| s.ord.to_s + ' ' } #=> "104 ello"
4331  * "hello".sub(/(?<foo>[aeiou])/, '*\k<foo>*') #=> "h*e*llo"
4332  * 'Is SHELL your preferred shell?'.sub(/[[:upper:]]{2,}/, ENV)
4333  * #=> "Is /bin/bash your preferred shell?"
4334  */
4335 
4336 static VALUE
4337 rb_str_sub(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str)
4338 {
4339  str = rb_str_dup(str);
4340  rb_str_sub_bang(argc, argv, str);
4341  return str;
4342 }
4343 
4344 static VALUE
4345 str_gsub(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str, int bang)
4346 {
4347  VALUE pat, val = Qnil, repl, match, match0 = Qnil, dest, hash = Qnil;
4348  struct re_registers *regs;
4349  long beg, n;
4350  long beg0, end0;
4351  long offset, blen, slen, len, last;
4352  enum {STR, ITER, MAP} mode = STR;
4353  char *sp, *cp;
4354  int tainted = 0;
4355  int need_backref = -1;
4356  rb_encoding *str_enc;
4357 
4358  switch (argc) {
4359  case 1:
4360  RETURN_ENUMERATOR(str, argc, argv);
4361  mode = ITER;
4362  break;
4363  case 2:
4364  repl = argv[1];
4365  hash = rb_check_hash_type(argv[1]);
4366  if (NIL_P(hash)) {
4367  StringValue(repl);
4368  }
4369  else {
4370  mode = MAP;
4371  }
4372  if (OBJ_TAINTED(repl)) tainted = 1;
4373  break;
4374  default:
4375  rb_check_arity(argc, 1, 2);
4376  }
4377 
4378  pat = get_pat_quoted(argv[0], 1);
4379  beg = rb_pat_search(pat, str, 0, need_backref);
4380  if (beg < 0) {
4381  if (bang) return Qnil; /* no match, no substitution */
4382  return rb_str_dup(str);
4383  }
4384 
4385  offset = 0;
4386  n = 0;
4387  blen = RSTRING_LEN(str) + 30; /* len + margin */
4388  dest = rb_str_buf_new(blen);
4389  sp = RSTRING_PTR(str);
4390  slen = RSTRING_LEN(str);
4391  cp = sp;
4392  str_enc = STR_ENC_GET(str);
4393  rb_enc_associate(dest, str_enc);
4394  ENC_CODERANGE_SET(dest, rb_enc_asciicompat(str_enc) ? ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT : ENC_CODERANGE_VALID);
4395 
4396  do {
4397  n++;
4398 
4399  match = rb_backref_get();
4400  regs = RMATCH_REGS(match);
4401  if (RB_TYPE_P(pat, T_STRING)) {
4402  beg0 = beg;
4403  end0 = beg0 + RSTRING_LEN(pat);
4404  match0 = pat;
4405  }
4406  else {
4407  beg0 = BEG(0);
4408  end0 = END(0);
4409  if (mode == ITER) match0 = rb_reg_nth_match(0, match);
4410  }
4411 
4412  if (mode) {
4413  if (mode == ITER) {
4414  val = rb_obj_as_string(rb_yield(match0));
4415  }
4416  else {
4417  val = rb_hash_aref(hash, rb_str_subseq(str, beg0, end0 - beg0));
4418  val = rb_obj_as_string(val);
4419  }
4420  str_mod_check(str, sp, slen);
4421  if (val == dest) { /* paranoid check [ruby-dev:24827] */
4422  rb_raise(rb_eRuntimeError, "block should not cheat");
4423  }
4424  }
4425  else if (need_backref) {
4426  val = rb_reg_regsub(repl, str, regs, RB_TYPE_P(pat, T_STRING) ? Qnil : pat);
4427  if (need_backref < 0) {
4428  need_backref = val != repl;
4429  }
4430  }
4431  else {
4432  val = repl;
4433  }
4434 
4435 
4436  if (OBJ_TAINTED(val)) tainted = 1;
4437 
4438  len = beg0 - offset; /* copy pre-match substr */
4439  if (len) {
4440  rb_enc_str_buf_cat(dest, cp, len, str_enc);
4441  }
4442 
4443  rb_str_buf_append(dest, val);
4444 
4445  last = offset;
4446  offset = end0;
4447  if (beg0 == end0) {
4448  /*
4449  * Always consume at least one character of the input string
4450  * in order to prevent infinite loops.
4451  */
4452  if (RSTRING_LEN(str) <= end0) break;
4453  len = rb_enc_fast_mbclen(RSTRING_PTR(str)+end0, RSTRING_END(str), str_enc);
4454  rb_enc_str_buf_cat(dest, RSTRING_PTR(str)+end0, len, str_enc);
4455  offset = end0 + len;
4456  }
4457  cp = RSTRING_PTR(str) + offset;
4458  if (offset > RSTRING_LEN(str)) break;
4459  beg = rb_pat_search(pat, str, offset, need_backref);
4460  } while (beg >= 0);
4461  if (RSTRING_LEN(str) > offset) {
4462  rb_enc_str_buf_cat(dest, cp, RSTRING_LEN(str) - offset, str_enc);
4463  }
4464  rb_pat_search(pat, str, last, 1);
4465  if (bang) {
4466  rb_str_shared_replace(str, dest);
4467  }
4468  else {
4469  RBASIC_SET_CLASS(dest, rb_obj_class(str));
4470  OBJ_INFECT(dest, str);
4471  str = dest;
4472  }
4473 
4474  if (tainted) OBJ_TAINT(str);
4475  return str;
4476 }

4479 /*
4480  * call-seq:
4481  * str.gsub!(pattern, replacement) -> str or nil
4482  * str.gsub!(pattern) {|match| block } -> str or nil
4483  * str.gsub!(pattern) -> an_enumerator
4484  *
4485  * Performs the substitutions of <code>String#gsub</code> in place, returning
4486  * <i>str</i>, or <code>nil</code> if no substitutions were performed.
4487  * If no block and no <i>replacement</i> is given, an enumerator is returned instead.
4488  */
4489 
4490 static VALUE
4491 rb_str_gsub_bang(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str)
4492 {
4493  str_modify_keep_cr(str);
4494  return str_gsub(argc, argv, str, 1);
4495 }
4496 
4497 
4498 /*
4499  * call-seq:
4500  * str.gsub(pattern, replacement) -> new_str
4501  * str.gsub(pattern, hash) -> new_str
4502  * str.gsub(pattern) {|match| block } -> new_str
4503  * str.gsub(pattern) -> enumerator
4504  *
4505  * Returns a copy of <i>str</i> with the <em>all</em> occurrences of
4506  * <i>pattern</i> substituted for the second argument. The <i>pattern</i> is
4507  * typically a <code>Regexp</code>; if given as a <code>String</code>, any
4508  * regular expression metacharacters it contains will be interpreted
4509  * literally, e.g. <code>'\\\d'</code> will match a backlash followed by 'd',
4510  * instead of a digit.
4511  *
4512  * If <i>replacement</i> is a <code>String</code> it will be substituted for
4513  * the matched text. It may contain back-references to the pattern's capture
4514  * groups of the form <code>\\\d</code>, where <i>d</i> is a group number, or
4515  * <code>\\\k<n></code>, where <i>n</i> is a group name. If it is a
4516  * double-quoted string, both back-references must be preceded by an
4517  * additional backslash. However, within <i>replacement</i> the special match
4518  * variables, such as <code>$&</code>, will not refer to the current match.
4519  *
4520  * If the second argument is a <code>Hash</code>, and the matched text is one
4521  * of its keys, the corresponding value is the replacement string.
4522  *
4523  * In the block form, the current match string is passed in as a parameter,
4524  * and variables such as <code>$1</code>, <code>$2</code>, <code>$`</code>,
4525  * <code>$&</code>, and <code>$'</code> will be set appropriately. The value
4526  * returned by the block will be substituted for the match on each call.
4527  *
4528  * The result inherits any tainting in the original string or any supplied
4529  * replacement string.
4530  *
4531  * When neither a block nor a second argument is supplied, an
4532  * <code>Enumerator</code> is returned.
4533  *
4534  * "hello".gsub(/[aeiou]/, '*') #=> "h*ll*"
4535  * "hello".gsub(/([aeiou])/, '<\1>') #=> "h<e>ll<o>"
4536  * "hello".gsub(/./) {|s| s.ord.to_s + ' '} #=> "104 101 108 108 111 "
4537  * "hello".gsub(/(?<foo>[aeiou])/, '{\k<foo>}') #=> "h{e}ll{o}"
4538  * 'hello'.gsub(/[eo]/, 'e' => 3, 'o' => '*') #=> "h3ll*"
4539  */
4540 
4541 static VALUE
4542 rb_str_gsub(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str)
4543 {
4544  return str_gsub(argc, argv, str, 0);
4545 }
4546

4548 /*
4549  * call-seq:
4550  * str.replace(other_str) -> str
4551  *
4552  * Replaces the contents and taintedness of <i>str</i> with the corresponding
4553  * values in <i>other_str</i>.
4554  *
4555  * s = "hello" #=> "hello"
4556  * s.replace "world" #=> "world"
4557  */
4558 
4559 VALUE
4560 rb_str_replace(VALUE str, VALUE str2)
4561 {
4562  str_modifiable(str);
4563  if (str == str2) return str;
4564 
4565  StringValue(str2);
4566  str_discard(str);
4567  return str_replace(str, str2);
4568 }

4635 static VALUE
4636 rb_str_setbyte(VALUE str, VALUE index, VALUE value)
4637 {

4639  int byte = NUM2INT(value);
4640  long len = RSTRING_LEN(str);
4641 
4642  if (pos < -len || len <= pos)
4643  rb_raise(rb_eIndexError, "index %ld out of string", pos);
4644  if (pos < 0)
4645  pos += len;

4650

4654 static VALUE
4655 str_byte_substr(VALUE str, long beg, long len)
4656 {
4657  char *p, *s = RSTRING_PTR(str);
4658  long n = RSTRING_LEN(str);
4659  VALUE str2;
4660 
4661  if (beg > n || len < 0) return Qnil;
4662  if (beg < 0) {
4663  beg += n;
4664  if (beg < 0) return Qnil;
4665  }
4666  if (beg + len > n)
4667  len = n - beg;
4668  if (len <= 0) {
4669  len = 0;
4670  p = 0;
4671  }
4672  else
4673  p = s + beg;
4674 
4675  if (len > RSTRING_EMBED_LEN_MAX && SHARABLE_SUBSTRING_P(beg, len, n)) {
4676  str2 = rb_str_new_frozen(str);
4677  str2 = str_new_shared(rb_obj_class(str2), str2);
4678  RSTRING(str2)->as.heap.ptr += beg;
4679  RSTRING(str2)->as.heap.len = len;
4680  }
4681  else {
4682  str2 = rb_str_new_with_class(str, p, len);
4683  }
4684 
4685  str_enc_copy(str2, str);
4686 
4687  if (RSTRING_LEN(str2) == 0) {
4688  if (!rb_enc_asciicompat(STR_ENC_GET(str)))
4689  ENC_CODERANGE_SET(str2, ENC_CODERANGE_VALID);
4690  else
4691  ENC_CODERANGE_SET(str2, ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT);
4692  }
4693  else {
4694  switch (ENC_CODERANGE(str)) {
4695  case ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT:
4696  ENC_CODERANGE_SET(str2, ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT);
4697  break;
4698  default:
4699  ENC_CODERANGE_SET(str2, ENC_CODERANGE_UNKNOWN);
4700  break;
4701  }
4702  }
4703 
4704  OBJ_INFECT(str2, str);
4705 
4706  return str2;
4707 }

4709 static VALUE
4710 str_byte_aref(VALUE str, VALUE indx)
4711 {
4712  long idx;
4713  switch (TYPE(indx)) {
4714  case T_FIXNUM:
4715  idx = FIX2LONG(indx);
4716 
4717  num_index:
4718  str = str_byte_substr(str, idx, 1);
4719  if (NIL_P(str) || RSTRING_LEN(str) == 0) return Qnil;
4720  return str;
4721 
4722  default:
4723  /* check if indx is Range */
4724  {
4725  long beg, len = RSTRING_LEN(str);
4726 
4727  switch (rb_range_beg_len(indx, &beg, &len, len, 0)) {
4728  case Qfalse:
4729  break;
4730  case Qnil:
4731  return Qnil;
4732  default:
4733  return str_byte_substr(str, beg, len);
4734  }
4735  }
4736  idx = NUM2LONG(indx);
4737  goto num_index;
4738  }
4739 
4740  UNREACHABLE;
4741 }

4743 /*
4744  * call-seq:
4745  * str.byteslice(fixnum) -> new_str or nil
4746  * str.byteslice(fixnum, fixnum) -> new_str or nil
4747  * str.byteslice(range) -> new_str or nil
4748  *
4749  * Byte Reference---If passed a single <code>Fixnum</code>, returns a
4750  * substring of one byte at that position. If passed two <code>Fixnum</code>
4751  * objects, returns a substring starting at the offset given by the first, and
4752  * a length given by the second. If given a <code>Range</code>, a substring containing
4753  * bytes at offsets given by the range is returned. In all three cases, if
4754  * an offset is negative, it is counted from the end of <i>str</i>. Returns
4755  * <code>nil</code> if the initial offset falls outside the string, the length
4756  * is negative, or the beginning of the range is greater than the end.
4757  * The encoding of the resulted string keeps original encoding.
4758  *
4759  * "hello".byteslice(1) #=> "e"
4760  * "hello".byteslice(-1) #=> "o"
4761  * "hello".byteslice(1, 2) #=> "el"
4762  * "\x80\u3042".byteslice(1, 3) #=> "\u3042"
4763  * "\x03\u3042\xff".byteslice(1..3) #=> "\u3042"
4764  */
4765 
4766 static VALUE
4767 rb_str_byteslice(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str)
4768 {
4769  if (argc == 2) {
4770  return str_byte_substr(str, NUM2LONG(argv[0]), NUM2LONG(argv[1]));
4771  }
4772  rb_check_arity(argc, 1, 2);
4773  return str_byte_aref(str, argv[0]);
4774 }

4776 /*
4777  * call-seq:
4778  * str.reverse -> new_str
4779  *
4780  * Returns a new string with the characters from <i>str</i> in reverse order.
4781  *
4782  * "stressed".reverse #=> "desserts"
4783  */
4784 
4785 static VALUE
4786 rb_str_reverse(VALUE str)
4787 {
4788  rb_encoding *enc;
4789  VALUE rev;
4790  char *s, *e, *p;
4791  int single = 1;
4792 
4793  if (RSTRING_LEN(str) <= 1) return rb_str_dup(str);
4794  enc = STR_ENC_GET(str);
4795  rev = rb_str_new_with_class(str, 0, RSTRING_LEN(str));
4796  s = RSTRING_PTR(str); e = RSTRING_END(str);
4797  p = RSTRING_END(rev);
4798 
4799  if (RSTRING_LEN(str) > 1) {
4800  if (single_byte_optimizable(str)) {
4801  while (s < e) {
4802  *--p = *s++;
4803  }
4804  }
4805  else if (ENC_CODERANGE(str) == ENC_CODERANGE_VALID) {
4806  while (s < e) {
4807  int clen = rb_enc_fast_mbclen(s, e, enc);
4808 
4809  if (clen > 1 || (*s & 0x80)) single = 0;
4810  p -= clen;
4811  memcpy(p, s, clen);
4812  s += clen;
4813  }
4814  }
4815  else {
4816  while (s < e) {
4817  int clen = rb_enc_mbclen(s, e, enc);
4818 
4819  if (clen > 1 || (*s & 0x80)) single = 0;
4820  p -= clen;
4821  memcpy(p, s, clen);
4822  s += clen;
4823  }
4824  }
4825  }
4826  STR_SET_LEN(rev, RSTRING_LEN(str));
4827  OBJ_INFECT(rev, str);
4828  if (ENC_CODERANGE(str) == ENC_CODERANGE_UNKNOWN) {
4829  if (single) {
4830  ENC_CODERANGE_SET(str, ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT);
4831  }
4832  else {
4833  ENC_CODERANGE_SET(str, ENC_CODERANGE_VALID);
4834  }
4835  }
4836  rb_enc_cr_str_copy_for_substr(rev, str);
4837 
4838  return rev;
4839 }

4843  * call-seq:
4844  * str.reverse! -> str
4845  *
4846  * Reverses <i>str</i> in place.
4847  */
4848 
4849 static VALUE
4850 rb_str_reverse_bang(VALUE str)
4851 {
4852  if (RSTRING_LEN(str) > 1) {
4853  if (single_byte_optimizable(str)) {
4854  char *s, *e, c;
4855 
4856  str_modify_keep_cr(str);
4857  s = RSTRING_PTR(str);
4858  e = RSTRING_END(str) - 1;
4859  while (s < e) {
4860  c = *s;
4861  *s++ = *e;
4862  *e-- = c;
4863  }
4864  }
4865  else {
4866  rb_str_shared_replace(str, rb_str_reverse(str));
4867  }
4868  }
4869  else {
4870  str_modify_keep_cr(str);
4871  }
4872  return str;
4873 }

4901 /*
4902  * call-seq:
4903  * str.to_i(base=10) -> integer
4904  *
4905  * Returns the result of interpreting leading characters in <i>str</i> as an
4906  * integer base <i>base</i> (between 2 and 36). Extraneous characters past the
4907  * end of a valid number are ignored. If there is not a valid number at the
4908  * start of <i>str</i>, <code>0</code> is returned. This method never raises an
4909  * exception when <i>base</i> is valid.
4910  *
4911  * "12345".to_i #=> 12345
4912  * "99 red balloons".to_i #=> 99
4913  * "0a".to_i #=> 0
4914  * "0a".to_i(16) #=> 10
4915  * "hello".to_i #=> 0
4916  * "1100101".to_i(2) #=> 101
4917  * "1100101".to_i(8) #=> 294977
4918  * "1100101".to_i(10) #=> 1100101
4919  * "1100101".to_i(16) #=> 17826049
4920  */
4921 
4922 static VALUE
4923 rb_str_to_i(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str)
4924 {
4925  int base;
4926 
4927  if (argc == 0) base = 10;
4928  else {
4929  VALUE b;
4930 
4931  rb_scan_args(argc, argv, "01", &b);
4932  base = NUM2INT(b);
4933  }
4934  if (base < 0) {
4935  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "invalid radix %d", base);
4936  }
4937  return rb_str_to_inum(str, base, FALSE);
4938 }

4943  * str.to_f -> float
4944  *
4945  * Returns the result of interpreting leading characters in <i>str</i> as a
4946  * floating point number. Extraneous characters past the end of a valid number
4947  * are ignored. If there is not a valid number at the start of <i>str</i>,

4993 #define CHAR_ESC_LEN 13 /* sizeof(\x{ hex of 32bit unsigned int } \0) */
4994 
4995 int
4996 rb_str_buf_cat_escaped_char(VALUE result, unsigned int c, int unicode_p)
4997 {
4998  char buf[CHAR_ESC_LEN + 1];
4999  int l;
5000 
5001 #if SIZEOF_INT > 4
5002  c &= 0xffffffff;
5003 #endif
5004  if (unicode_p) {
5005  if (c < 0x7F && ISPRINT(c)) {
5006  snprintf(buf, CHAR_ESC_LEN, "%c", c);
5007  }
5008  else if (c < 0x10000) {
5009  snprintf(buf, CHAR_ESC_LEN, "\\u%04X", c);
5010  }
5011  else {
5012  snprintf(buf, CHAR_ESC_LEN, "\\u{%X}", c);
5013  }
5014  }
5015  else {
5016  if (c < 0x100) {
5017  snprintf(buf, CHAR_ESC_LEN, "\\x%02X", c);
5018  }
5019  else {
5020  snprintf(buf, CHAR_ESC_LEN, "\\x{%X}", c);
5021  }
5022  }
5023  l = (int)strlen(buf); /* CHAR_ESC_LEN cannot exceed INT_MAX */
5024  rb_str_buf_cat(result, buf, l);
5025  return l;
5026 }
5027 
5028 /*
5029  * call-seq:
5030  * str.inspect -> string
5031  *
5032  * Returns a printable version of _str_, surrounded by quote marks,
5033  * with special characters escaped.
5034  *
5035  * str = "hello"
5036  * str[3] = "\b"
5037  * str.inspect #=> "\"hel\\bo\""
5038  */
5039 
5040 VALUE
5041 rb_str_inspect(VALUE str)
5042 {
5043  int encidx = ENCODING_GET(str);
5044  rb_encoding *enc = rb_enc_from_index(encidx), *actenc;
5045  const char *p, *pend, *prev;
5046  char buf[CHAR_ESC_LEN + 1];
5047  VALUE result = rb_str_buf_new(0);
5048  rb_encoding *resenc = rb_default_internal_encoding();
5049  int unicode_p = rb_enc_unicode_p(enc);
5050  int asciicompat = rb_enc_asciicompat(enc);
5051 
5052  if (resenc == NULL) resenc = rb_default_external_encoding();
5053  if (!rb_enc_asciicompat(resenc)) resenc = rb_usascii_encoding();
5054  rb_enc_associate(result, resenc);
5055  str_buf_cat2(result, "\"");
5056 
5057  p = RSTRING_PTR(str); pend = RSTRING_END(str);
5058  prev = p;
5059  actenc = get_actual_encoding(encidx, str);
5060  if (actenc != enc) {
5061  enc = actenc;
5062  if (unicode_p) unicode_p = rb_enc_unicode_p(enc);
5063  }
5064  while (p < pend) {
5065  unsigned int c, cc;
5066  int n;
5067 
5068  n = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(p, pend, enc);
5069  if (!MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(n)) {
5070  if (p > prev) str_buf_cat(result, prev, p - prev);
5071  n = rb_enc_mbminlen(enc);
5072  if (pend < p + n)
5073  n = (int)(pend - p);
5074  while (n--) {
5075  snprintf(buf, CHAR_ESC_LEN, "\\x%02X", *p & 0377);
5076  str_buf_cat(result, buf, strlen(buf));
5077  prev = ++p;
5078  }
5079  continue;
5080  }
5081  n = MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_LEN(n);
5082  c = rb_enc_mbc_to_codepoint(p, pend, enc);
5083  p += n;
5084  if ((asciicompat || unicode_p) &&
5085  (c == '"'|| c == '\\' ||
5086  (c == '#' &&
5087  p < pend &&
5088  MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(rb_enc_precise_mbclen(p,pend,enc)) &&
5089  (cc = rb_enc_codepoint(p,pend,enc),
5090  (cc == '$' || cc == '@' || cc == '{'))))) {
5091  if (p - n > prev) str_buf_cat(result, prev, p - n - prev);
5092  str_buf_cat2(result, "\\");
5093  if (asciicompat || enc == resenc) {
5094  prev = p - n;
5095  continue;
5096  }
5097  }
5098  switch (c) {
5099  case '\n': cc = 'n'; break;
5100  case '\r': cc = 'r'; break;
5101  case '\t': cc = 't'; break;
5102  case '\f': cc = 'f'; break;
5103  case '\013': cc = 'v'; break;
5104  case '\010': cc = 'b'; break;
5105  case '\007': cc = 'a'; break;
5106  case 033: cc = 'e'; break;
5107  default: cc = 0; break;
5108  }
5109  if (cc) {
5110  if (p - n > prev) str_buf_cat(result, prev, p - n - prev);
5111  buf[0] = '\\';
5112  buf[1] = (char)cc;
5113  str_buf_cat(result, buf, 2);
5114  prev = p;
5115  continue;
5116  }
5117  if ((enc == resenc && rb_enc_isprint(c, enc)) ||
5118  (asciicompat && rb_enc_isascii(c, enc) && ISPRINT(c))) {
5119  continue;
5120  }
5121  else {
5122  if (p - n > prev) str_buf_cat(result, prev, p - n - prev);
5123  rb_str_buf_cat_escaped_char(result, c, unicode_p);
5124  prev = p;
5125  continue;
5126  }
5127  }
5128  if (p > prev) str_buf_cat(result, prev, p - prev);
5129  str_buf_cat2(result, "\"");
5130 
5131  OBJ_INFECT(result, str);
5132  return result;
5133 }
5134 
5135 #define IS_EVSTR(p,e) ((p) < (e) && (*(p) == '$' || *(p) == '@' || *(p) == '{'))
5136 
5137 /*
5138  * call-seq:
5139  * str.dump -> new_str
5140  *
5141  * Produces a version of +str+ with all non-printing characters replaced by
5142  * <code>\nnn</code> notation and all special characters escaped.
5143  *
5144  * "hello \n ''".dump #=> "\"hello \\n ''\"
5145  */
5146 
5147 VALUE
5148 rb_str_dump(VALUE str)
5149 {
5150  rb_encoding *enc = rb_enc_get(str);
5151  long len;
5152  const char *p, *pend;
5153  char *q, *qend;
5154  VALUE result;
5155  int u8 = (enc == rb_utf8_encoding());
5156 
5157  len = 2; /* "" */
5158  p = RSTRING_PTR(str); pend = p + RSTRING_LEN(str);
5159  while (p < pend) {
5160  unsigned char c = *p++;
5161  switch (c) {
5162  case '"': case '\\':
5163  case '\n': case '\r':
5164  case '\t': case '\f':
5165  case '\013': case '\010': case '\007': case '\033':
5166  len += 2;
5167  break;
5168 
5169  case '#':
5170  len += IS_EVSTR(p, pend) ? 2 : 1;
5171  break;
5172 
5173  default:
5174  if (ISPRINT(c)) {
5175  len++;
5176  }
5177  else {
5178  if (u8 && c > 0x7F) { /* \u{NN} */
5179  int n = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(p-1, pend, enc);
5180  if (MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(n)) {
5181  unsigned int cc = rb_enc_mbc_to_codepoint(p-1, pend, enc);
5182  while (cc >>= 4) len++;
5183  len += 5;
5184  p += MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_LEN(n)-1;
5185  break;
5186  }
5187  }
5188  len += 4; /* \xNN */
5189  }
5190  break;
5191  }
5192  }
5193  if (!rb_enc_asciicompat(enc)) {
5194  len += 19; /* ".force_encoding('')" */
5195  len += strlen(enc->name);
5196  }
5197 
5198  result = rb_str_new_with_class(str, 0, len);
5199  p = RSTRING_PTR(str); pend = p + RSTRING_LEN(str);
5200  q = RSTRING_PTR(result); qend = q + len + 1;
5201 
5202  *q++ = '"';
5203  while (p < pend) {
5204  unsigned char c = *p++;
5205 
5206  if (c == '"' || c == '\\') {
5207  *q++ = '\\';
5208  *q++ = c;
5209  }
5210  else if (c == '#') {
5211  if (IS_EVSTR(p, pend)) *q++ = '\\';
5212  *q++ = '#';
5213  }
5214  else if (c == '\n') {
5215  *q++ = '\\';
5216  *q++ = 'n';
5217  }
5218  else if (c == '\r') {
5219  *q++ = '\\';
5220  *q++ = 'r';
5221  }
5222  else if (c == '\t') {
5223  *q++ = '\\';
5224  *q++ = 't';
5225  }
5226  else if (c == '\f') {
5227  *q++ = '\\';
5228  *q++ = 'f';
5229  }
5230  else if (c == '\013') {
5231  *q++ = '\\';
5232  *q++ = 'v';
5233  }
5234  else if (c == '\010') {
5235  *q++ = '\\';
5236  *q++ = 'b';
5237  }
5238  else if (c == '\007') {
5239  *q++ = '\\';
5240  *q++ = 'a';
5241  }
5242  else if (c == '\033') {
5243  *q++ = '\\';
5244  *q++ = 'e';
5245  }
5246  else if (ISPRINT(c)) {
5247  *q++ = c;
5248  }
5249  else {
5250  *q++ = '\\';
5251  if (u8) {
5252  int n = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(p-1, pend, enc) - 1;
5253  if (MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(n)) {
5254  int cc = rb_enc_mbc_to_codepoint(p-1, pend, enc);
5255  p += n;
5256  snprintf(q, qend-q, "u{%x}", cc);
5257  q += strlen(q);
5258  continue;
5259  }
5260  }
5261  snprintf(q, qend-q, "x%02X", c);
5262  q += 3;
5263  }
5264  }
5265  *q++ = '"';
5266  *q = '\0';
5267  if (!rb_enc_asciicompat(enc)) {
5268  snprintf(q, qend-q, ".force_encoding(\"%s\")", enc->name);
5269  enc = rb_ascii8bit_encoding();
5270  }
5271  OBJ_INFECT(result, str);
5272  /* result from dump is ASCII */
5273  rb_enc_associate(result, enc);
5274  ENC_CODERANGE_SET(result, ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT);
5275  return result;
5276 }

5279 static void
5280 rb_str_check_dummy_enc(rb_encoding *enc)
5281 {
5282  if (rb_enc_dummy_p(enc)) {
5283  rb_raise(rb_eEncCompatError, "incompatible encoding with this operation: %s",
5284  rb_enc_name(enc));
5285  }
5286 }

5288 /*
5289  * call-seq:
5290  * str.upcase! -> str or nil
5291  *
5292  * Upcases the contents of <i>str</i>, returning <code>nil</code> if no changes
5293  * were made.
5294  * Note: case replacement is effective only in ASCII region.
5295  */
5296 
5297 static VALUE
5298 rb_str_upcase_bang(VALUE str)
5299 {
5300  rb_encoding *enc;
5301  char *s, *send;
5302  int modify = 0;
5303  int n;
5304 
5305  str_modify_keep_cr(str);
5306  enc = STR_ENC_GET(str);
5307  rb_str_check_dummy_enc(enc);
5308  s = RSTRING_PTR(str); send = RSTRING_END(str);
5309  if (single_byte_optimizable(str)) {
5310  while (s < send) {
5311  unsigned int c = *(unsigned char*)s;
5312 
5313  if (rb_enc_isascii(c, enc) && 'a' <= c && c <= 'z') {
5314  *s = 'A' + (c - 'a');
5315  modify = 1;
5316  }
5317  s++;
5318  }
5319  }
5320  else {
5321  int ascompat = rb_enc_asciicompat(enc);
5322 
5323  while (s < send) {
5324  unsigned int c;
5325 
5326  if (ascompat && (c = *(unsigned char*)s) < 0x80) {
5327  if (rb_enc_isascii(c, enc) && 'a' <= c && c <= 'z') {
5328  *s = 'A' + (c - 'a');
5329  modify = 1;
5330  }
5331  s++;
5332  }
5333  else {
5334  c = rb_enc_codepoint_len(s, send, &n, enc);
5335  if (rb_enc_islower(c, enc)) {
5336  /* assuming toupper returns codepoint with same size */
5337  rb_enc_mbcput(rb_enc_toupper(c, enc), s, enc);
5338  modify = 1;
5339  }
5340  s += n;
5341  }
5342  }
5343  }
5344 
5345  if (modify) return str;
5346  return Qnil;
5347 }
5348

5350 /*
5351  * call-seq:
5352  * str.upcase -> new_str
5353  *
5354  * Returns a copy of <i>str</i> with all lowercase letters replaced with their
5355  * uppercase counterparts. The operation is locale insensitive---only
5356  * characters ``a'' to ``z'' are affected.
5357  * Note: case replacement is effective only in ASCII region.
5358  *
5359  * "hEllO".upcase #=> "HELLO"
5360  */
5361 
5362 static VALUE
5363 rb_str_upcase(VALUE str)
5364 {
5365  str = rb_str_dup(str);
5366  rb_str_upcase_bang(str);
5367  return str;
5368 }

5376  * changes were made.
5377  * Note: case replacement is effective only in ASCII region.

5380 static VALUE

5394

5396  *s = 'a' + (c - 'A');
5397  modify = 1;
5398  }
5399  s++;
5400  }
5401  }
5402  else {
5403  int ascompat = rb_enc_asciicompat(enc);
5404

5406  unsigned int c;
5407  int n;
5408

5410  if (rb_enc_isascii(c, enc) && 'A' <= c && c <= 'Z') {
5411  *s = 'a' + (c - 'A');
5412  modify = 1;
5413  }

5415  }
5416  else {
5417  c = rb_enc_codepoint_len(s, send, &n, enc);
5418  if (rb_enc_isupper(c, enc)) {

5421  modify = 1;
5422  }
5423  s += n;

5426  }

5454 /*
5455  * call-seq:
5456  * str.capitalize! -> str or nil
5457  *
5458  * Modifies <i>str</i> by converting the first character to uppercase and the
5459  * remainder to lowercase. Returns <code>nil</code> if no changes are made.
5460  * Note: case conversion is effective only in ASCII region.
5461  *
5462  * a = "hello"
5463  * a.capitalize! #=> "Hello"
5464  * a #=> "Hello"
5465  * a.capitalize! #=> nil
5466  */
5467 
5468 static VALUE
5469 rb_str_capitalize_bang(VALUE str)
5470 {
5471  rb_encoding *enc;
5472  char *s, *send;
5473  int modify = 0;
5474  unsigned int c;
5475  int n;
5476 
5477  str_modify_keep_cr(str);
5478  enc = STR_ENC_GET(str);
5479  rb_str_check_dummy_enc(enc);
5480  if (RSTRING_LEN(str) == 0 || !RSTRING_PTR(str)) return Qnil;
5481  s = RSTRING_PTR(str); send = RSTRING_END(str);
5482 
5483  c = rb_enc_codepoint_len(s, send, &n, enc);
5484  if (rb_enc_islower(c, enc)) {
5485  rb_enc_mbcput(rb_enc_toupper(c, enc), s, enc);
5486  modify = 1;
5487  }
5488  s += n;
5489  while (s < send) {
5490  c = rb_enc_codepoint_len(s, send, &n, enc);
5491  if (rb_enc_isupper(c, enc)) {
5492  rb_enc_mbcput(rb_enc_tolower(c, enc), s, enc);
5493  modify = 1;
5494  }
5495  s += n;
5496  }
5497 
5498  if (modify) return str;
5499  return Qnil;
5500 }

5504  * call-seq:
5505  * str.capitalize -> new_str
5506  *

5508  * and the remainder to lowercase.
5509  * Note: case conversion is effective only in ASCII region.

5586 
5587 typedef unsigned char *USTR;
5588 
5589 struct tr {
5590  int gen;
5591  unsigned int now, max;
5592  char *p, *pend;
5593 };
5594 
5595 static unsigned int
5596 trnext(struct tr *t, rb_encoding *enc)
5597 {
5598  int n;
5599 
5600  for (;;) {
5601  if (!t->gen) {
5602 nextpart:
5603  if (t->p == t->pend) return -1;
5604  if (rb_enc_ascget(t->p, t->pend, &n, enc) == '\\' && t->p + n < t->pend) {
5605  t->p += n;
5606  }
5607  t->now = rb_enc_codepoint_len(t->p, t->pend, &n, enc);
5608  t->p += n;
5609  if (rb_enc_ascget(t->p, t->pend, &n, enc) == '-' && t->p + n < t->pend) {
5610  t->p += n;
5611  if (t->p < t->pend) {
5612  unsigned int c = rb_enc_codepoint_len(t->p, t->pend, &n, enc);
5613  t->p += n;
5614  if (t->now > c) {
5615  if (t->now < 0x80 && c < 0x80) {
5616  rb_raise(rb_eArgError,
5617  "invalid range \"%c-%c\" in string transliteration",
5618  t->now, c);
5619  }
5620  else {
5621  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "invalid range in string transliteration");
5622  }
5623  continue; /* not reached */
5624  }
5625  t->gen = 1;
5626  t->max = c;
5627  }
5628  }
5629  return t->now;
5630  }
5631  else {
5632  while (ONIGENC_CODE_TO_MBCLEN(enc, ++t->now) <= 0) {
5633  if (t->now == t->max) {
5634  t->gen = 0;
5635  goto nextpart;
5636  }
5637  }
5638  if (t->now < t->max) {
5639  return t->now;
5640  }
5641  else {
5642  t->gen = 0;
5643  return t->max;
5644  }
5645  }
5646  }
5647 }
5648 
5649 static VALUE rb_str_delete_bang(int,VALUE*,VALUE);
5650 
5651 static VALUE
5652 tr_trans(VALUE str, VALUE src, VALUE repl, int sflag)
5653 {
5654  const unsigned int errc = -1;
5655  unsigned int trans[256];
5656  rb_encoding *enc, *e1, *e2;
5657  struct tr trsrc, trrepl;
5658  int cflag = 0;
5659  unsigned int c, c0, last = 0;
5660  int modify = 0, i, l;
5661  char *s, *send;
5662  VALUE hash = 0;
5663  int singlebyte = single_byte_optimizable(str);
5664  int cr;
5665 
5666 #define CHECK_IF_ASCII(c) \
5667  (void)((cr == ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT && !rb_isascii(c)) ? \
5668  (cr = ENC_CODERANGE_VALID) : 0)
5669 
5670  StringValue(src);
5671  StringValue(repl);
5672  if (RSTRING_LEN(str) == 0 || !RSTRING_PTR(str)) return Qnil;
5673  if (RSTRING_LEN(repl) == 0) {
5674  return rb_str_delete_bang(1, &src, str);
5675  }
5676 
5677  cr = ENC_CODERANGE(str);
5678  e1 = rb_enc_check(str, src);
5679  e2 = rb_enc_check(str, repl);
5680  if (e1 == e2) {
5681  enc = e1;
5682  }
5683  else {
5684  enc = rb_enc_check(src, repl);
5685  }
5686  trsrc.p = RSTRING_PTR(src); trsrc.pend = trsrc.p + RSTRING_LEN(src);
5687  if (RSTRING_LEN(src) > 1 &&
5688  rb_enc_ascget(trsrc.p, trsrc.pend, &l, enc) == '^' &&
5689  trsrc.p + l < trsrc.pend) {
5690  cflag = 1;
5691  trsrc.p += l;
5692  }
5693  trrepl.p = RSTRING_PTR(repl);
5694  trrepl.pend = trrepl.p + RSTRING_LEN(repl);
5695  trsrc.gen = trrepl.gen = 0;
5696  trsrc.now = trrepl.now = 0;
5697  trsrc.max = trrepl.max = 0;
5698 
5699  if (cflag) {
5700  for (i=0; i<256; i++) {
5701  trans[i] = 1;
5702  }
5703  while ((c = trnext(&trsrc, enc)) != errc) {
5704  if (c < 256) {
5705  trans[c] = errc;
5706  }
5707  else {
5708  if (!hash) hash = rb_hash_new();
5709  rb_hash_aset(hash, UINT2NUM(c), Qtrue);
5710  }
5711  }
5712  while ((c = trnext(&trrepl, enc)) != errc)
5713  /* retrieve last replacer */;
5714  last = trrepl.now;
5715  for (i=0; i<256; i++) {
5716  if (trans[i] != errc) {
5717  trans[i] = last;
5718  }
5719  }
5720  }
5721  else {
5722  unsigned int r;
5723 
5724  for (i=0; i<256; i++) {
5725  trans[i] = errc;
5726  }
5727  while ((c = trnext(&trsrc, enc)) != errc) {
5728  r = trnext(&trrepl, enc);
5729  if (r == errc) r = trrepl.now;
5730  if (c < 256) {
5731  trans[c] = r;
5732  if (rb_enc_codelen(r, enc) != 1) singlebyte = 0;
5733  }
5734  else {
5735  if (!hash) hash = rb_hash_new();
5736  rb_hash_aset(hash, UINT2NUM(c), UINT2NUM(r));
5737  }
5738  }
5739  }
5740 
5741  if (cr == ENC_CODERANGE_VALID)
5742  cr = ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT;
5743  str_modify_keep_cr(str);
5744  s = RSTRING_PTR(str); send = RSTRING_END(str);
5745  if (sflag) {
5746  int clen, tlen;
5747  long offset, max = RSTRING_LEN(str);
5748  unsigned int save = -1;
5749  char *buf = ALLOC_N(char, max), *t = buf;
5750 
5751  while (s < send) {
5752  int may_modify = 0;
5753 
5754  c0 = c = rb_enc_codepoint_len(s, send, &clen, e1);
5755  tlen = enc == e1 ? clen : rb_enc_codelen(c, enc);
5756 
5757  s += clen;
5758  if (c < 256) {
5759  c = trans[c];
5760  }
5761  else if (hash) {
5762  VALUE tmp = rb_hash_lookup(hash, UINT2NUM(c));
5763  if (NIL_P(tmp)) {
5764  if (cflag) c = last;
5765  else c = errc;
5766  }
5767  else if (cflag) c = errc;
5768  else c = NUM2INT(tmp);
5769  }
5770  else {
5771  c = errc;
5772  }
5773  if (c != (unsigned int)-1) {
5774  if (save == c) {
5775  CHECK_IF_ASCII(c);
5776  continue;
5777  }
5778  save = c;
5779  tlen = rb_enc_codelen(c, enc);
5780  modify = 1;
5781  }
5782  else {
5783  save = -1;
5784  c = c0;
5785  if (enc != e1) may_modify = 1;
5786  }
5787  while (t - buf + tlen >= max) {
5788  offset = t - buf;
5789  max *= 2;
5790  REALLOC_N(buf, char, max);
5791  t = buf + offset;
5792  }
5793  rb_enc_mbcput(c, t, enc);
5794  if (may_modify && memcmp(s, t, tlen) != 0) {
5795  modify = 1;
5796  }
5797  CHECK_IF_ASCII(c);
5798  t += tlen;
5799  }
5800  if (!STR_EMBED_P(str)) {
5801  ruby_sized_xfree(STR_HEAP_PTR(str), STR_HEAP_SIZE(str));
5802  }
5803  TERM_FILL(t, rb_enc_mbminlen(enc));
5804  RSTRING(str)->as.heap.ptr = buf;
5805  RSTRING(str)->as.heap.len = t - buf;
5806  STR_SET_NOEMBED(str);
5807  RSTRING(str)->as.heap.aux.capa = max;
5808  }
5809  else if (rb_enc_mbmaxlen(enc) == 1 || (singlebyte && !hash)) {
5810  while (s < send) {
5811  c = (unsigned char)*s;
5812  if (trans[c] != errc) {
5813  if (!cflag) {
5814  c = trans[c];
5815  *s = c;
5816  modify = 1;
5817  }
5818  else {
5819  *s = last;
5820  modify = 1;
5821  }
5822  }
5823  CHECK_IF_ASCII(c);
5824  s++;
5825  }
5826  }
5827  else {
5828  int clen, tlen, max = (int)(RSTRING_LEN(str) * 1.2);
5829  long offset;
5830  char *buf = ALLOC_N(char, max), *t = buf;
5831 
5832  while (s < send) {
5833  int may_modify = 0;
5834  c0 = c = rb_enc_codepoint_len(s, send, &clen, e1);
5835  tlen = enc == e1 ? clen : rb_enc_codelen(c, enc);
5836 
5837  if (c < 256) {
5838  c = trans[c];
5839  }
5840  else if (hash) {
5841  VALUE tmp = rb_hash_lookup(hash, UINT2NUM(c));
5842  if (NIL_P(tmp)) {
5843  if (cflag) c = last;
5844  else c = errc;
5845  }
5846  else if (cflag) c = errc;
5847  else c = NUM2INT(tmp);
5848  }
5849  else {
5850  c = cflag ? last : errc;
5851  }
5852  if (c != errc) {
5853  tlen = rb_enc_codelen(c, enc);
5854  modify = 1;
5855  }
5856  else {
5857  c = c0;
5858  if (enc != e1) may_modify = 1;
5859  }
5860  while (t - buf + tlen >= max) {
5861  offset = t - buf;
5862  max *= 2;
5863  REALLOC_N(buf, char, max);
5864  t = buf + offset;
5865  }
5866  if (s != t) {
5867  rb_enc_mbcput(c, t, enc);
5868  if (may_modify && memcmp(s, t, tlen) != 0) {
5869  modify = 1;
5870  }
5871  }
5872  CHECK_IF_ASCII(c);
5873  s += clen;
5874  t += tlen;
5875  }
5876  if (!STR_EMBED_P(str)) {
5877  ruby_sized_xfree(STR_HEAP_PTR(str), STR_HEAP_SIZE(str));
5878  }
5879  TERM_FILL(t, rb_enc_mbminlen(enc));
5880  RSTRING(str)->as.heap.ptr = buf;
5881  RSTRING(str)->as.heap.len = t - buf;
5882  STR_SET_NOEMBED(str);
5883  RSTRING(str)->as.heap.aux.capa = max;
5884  }
5885 
5886  if (modify) {
5887  if (cr != ENC_CODERANGE_BROKEN)
5888  ENC_CODERANGE_SET(str, cr);
5889  rb_enc_associate(str, enc);
5890  return str;
5891  }
5892  return Qnil;
5893 }

5895 
5896 /*
5897  * call-seq:
5898  * str.tr!(from_str, to_str) -> str or nil
5899  *
5900  * Translates <i>str</i> in place, using the same rules as
5901  * <code>String#tr</code>. Returns <i>str</i>, or <code>nil</code> if no
5902  * changes were made.
5903  */
5904 
5905 static VALUE
5906 rb_str_tr_bang(VALUE str, VALUE src, VALUE repl)
5907 {
5908  return tr_trans(str, src, repl, 0);
5909 }
5910 
5911 
5912 /*
5913  * call-seq:
5914  * str.tr(from_str, to_str) => new_str
5915  *
5916  * Returns a copy of +str+ with the characters in +from_str+ replaced by the
5917  * corresponding characters in +to_str+. If +to_str+ is shorter than
5918  * +from_str+, it is padded with its last character in order to maintain the
5919  * correspondence.
5920  *
5921  * "hello".tr('el', 'ip') #=> "hippo"
5922  * "hello".tr('aeiou', '*') #=> "h*ll*"
5923  * "hello".tr('aeiou', 'AA*') #=> "hAll*"
5924  *
5925  * Both strings may use the <code>c1-c2</code> notation to denote ranges of
5926  * characters, and +from_str+ may start with a <code>^</code>, which denotes
5927  * all characters except those listed.
5928  *
5929  * "hello".tr('a-y', 'b-z') #=> "ifmmp"
5930  * "hello".tr('^aeiou', '*') #=> "*e**o"
5931  *
5932  * The backslash character <code></code> can be used to escape
5933  * <code>^</code> or <code>-</code> and is otherwise ignored unless it
5934  * appears at the end of a range or the end of the +from_str+ or +to_str+:
5935  *
5936  * "hello^world".tr("\\^aeiou", "*") #=> "h*ll**w*rld"
5937  * "hello-world".tr("a\\-eo", "*") #=> "h*ll**w*rld"
5938  *
5939  * "hello\r\nworld".tr("\r", "") #=> "hello\nworld"
5940  * "hello\r\nworld".tr("\\r", "") #=> "hello\r\nwold"
5941  * "hello\r\nworld".tr("\\\r", "") #=> "hello\nworld"
5942  *
5943  * "X['\\b']".tr("X\\", "") #=> "['b']"
5944  * "X['\\b']".tr("X-\\]", "") #=> "'b'"
5945  */
5946 
5947 static VALUE
5948 rb_str_tr(VALUE str, VALUE src, VALUE repl)
5949 {
5950  str = rb_str_dup(str);
5951  tr_trans(str, src, repl, 0);
5952  return str;
5953 }
5954 
5955 #define TR_TABLE_SIZE 257
5956 static void
5957 tr_setup_table(VALUE str, char stable[TR_TABLE_SIZE], int first,
5958  VALUE *tablep, VALUE *ctablep, rb_encoding *enc)
5959 {
5960  const unsigned int errc = -1;
5961  char buf[256];
5962  struct tr tr;
5963  unsigned int c;
5964  VALUE table = 0, ptable = 0;
5965  int i, l, cflag = 0;
5966 
5967  tr.p = RSTRING_PTR(str); tr.pend = tr.p + RSTRING_LEN(str);
5968  tr.gen = tr.now = tr.max = 0;
5969 
5970  if (RSTRING_LEN(str) > 1 && rb_enc_ascget(tr.p, tr.pend, &l, enc) == '^') {
5971  cflag = 1;
5972  tr.p += l;
5973  }
5974  if (first) {
5975  for (i=0; i<256; i++) {
5976  stable[i] = 1;
5977  }
5978  stable[256] = cflag;
5979  }
5980  else if (stable[256] && !cflag) {
5981  stable[256] = 0;
5982  }
5983  for (i=0; i<256; i++) {
5984  buf[i] = cflag;
5985  }
5986 
5987  while ((c = trnext(&tr, enc)) != errc) {
5988  if (c < 256) {
5989  buf[c & 0xff] = !cflag;
5990  }
5991  else {
5992  VALUE key = UINT2NUM(c);
5993 
5994  if (!table && (first || *tablep || stable[256])) {
5995  if (cflag) {
5996  ptable = *ctablep;
5997  table = ptable ? ptable : rb_hash_new();
5998  *ctablep = table;
5999  }
6000  else {
6001  table = rb_hash_new();
6002  ptable = *tablep;
6003  *tablep = table;
6004  }
6005  }
6006  if (table && (!ptable || (cflag ^ !NIL_P(rb_hash_aref(ptable, key))))) {
6007  rb_hash_aset(table, key, Qtrue);
6008  }
6009  }
6010  }
6011  for (i=0; i<256; i++) {
6012  stable[i] = stable[i] && buf[i];
6013  }
6014  if (!table && !cflag) {
6015  *tablep = 0;
6016  }
6017 }
6018 
6019 
6020 static int
6021 tr_find(unsigned int c, const char table[TR_TABLE_SIZE], VALUE del, VALUE nodel)
6022 {
6023  if (c < 256) {
6024  return table[c] != 0;
6025  }
6026  else {
6027  VALUE v = UINT2NUM(c);
6028 
6029  if (del) {
6030  if (!NIL_P(rb_hash_lookup(del, v)) &&
6031  (!nodel || NIL_P(rb_hash_lookup(nodel, v)))) {
6032  return TRUE;
6033  }
6034  }
6035  else if (nodel && !NIL_P(rb_hash_lookup(nodel, v))) {
6036  return FALSE;
6037  }
6038  return table[256] ? TRUE : FALSE;
6039  }
6040 }
6041 
6042 /*
6043  * call-seq:
6044  * str.delete!([other_str]+) -> str or nil
6045  *
6046  * Performs a <code>delete</code> operation in place, returning <i>str</i>, or
6047  * <code>nil</code> if <i>str</i> was not modified.
6048  */
6049 
6050 static VALUE
6051 rb_str_delete_bang(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str)
6052 {
6053  char squeez[TR_TABLE_SIZE];
6054  rb_encoding *enc = 0;
6055  char *s, *send, *t;
6056  VALUE del = 0, nodel = 0;
6057  int modify = 0;
6058  int i, ascompat, cr;
6059 
6060  if (RSTRING_LEN(str) == 0 || !RSTRING_PTR(str)) return Qnil;
6061  rb_check_arity(argc, 1, UNLIMITED_ARGUMENTS);
6062  for (i=0; i<argc; i++) {
6063  VALUE s = argv[i];
6064 
6065  StringValue(s);
6066  enc = rb_enc_check(str, s);
6067  tr_setup_table(s, squeez, i==0, &del, &nodel, enc);
6068  }
6069 
6070  str_modify_keep_cr(str);
6071  ascompat = rb_enc_asciicompat(enc);
6072  s = t = RSTRING_PTR(str);
6073  send = RSTRING_END(str);
6074  cr = ascompat ? ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT : ENC_CODERANGE_VALID;
6075  while (s < send) {
6076  unsigned int c;
6077  int clen;
6078 
6079  if (ascompat && (c = *(unsigned char*)s) < 0x80) {
6080  if (squeez[c]) {
6081  modify = 1;
6082  }
6083  else {
6084  if (t != s) *t = c;
6085  t++;
6086  }
6087  s++;
6088  }
6089  else {
6090  c = rb_enc_codepoint_len(s, send, &clen, enc);
6091 
6092  if (tr_find(c, squeez, del, nodel)) {
6093  modify = 1;
6094  }
6095  else {
6096  if (t != s) rb_enc_mbcput(c, t, enc);
6097  t += clen;
6098  if (cr == ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT) cr = ENC_CODERANGE_VALID;
6099  }
6100  s += clen;
6101  }
6102  }
6103  TERM_FILL(t, TERM_LEN(str));
6104  STR_SET_LEN(str, t - RSTRING_PTR(str));
6105  ENC_CODERANGE_SET(str, cr);
6106 
6107  if (modify) return str;
6108  return Qnil;
6109 }
6110 
6111 
6112 /*
6113  * call-seq:
6114  * str.delete([other_str]+) -> new_str
6115  *
6116  * Returns a copy of <i>str</i> with all characters in the intersection of its
6117  * arguments deleted. Uses the same rules for building the set of characters as
6118  * <code>String#count</code>.
6119  *
6120  * "hello".delete "l","lo" #=> "heo"
6121  * "hello".delete "lo" #=> "he"
6122  * "hello".delete "aeiou", "^e" #=> "hell"
6123  * "hello".delete "ej-m" #=> "ho"
6124  */
6125 
6126 static VALUE
6127 rb_str_delete(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE str)
6128 {
6129  str = rb_str_dup(str);
6130  rb_str_delete_bang(argc, argv, str);
6131  return str;
6132 }
